In this incredibly in-depth CBT Nuggets course, trainer Anthony Sequeira guides students through the troubleshooting of the Unified Computing System from Cisco (UCS). This includes B-series servers, C-series rack servers, the UCS chassis, Fabric Interconnects, and much more. This course also provides complete preparation for exam 642-035 DCUCT.

Recommended skills:
CCNA Data Center from CBT Nuggets or equivalent knowledge
Cisco CCNP Data Center 642-999 DCUCI from CBT Nuggets or equivalent knowledge

Recommended equipment:
The Cisco UCS emulator or practice UCS equipment

Related certifications:
CCNP Data Center
Cisco Unified Computing Support Specialist


The Cisco UCS system consists of many complex components that all interrelate in some way. Needless to say, much can go wrong with this system. This course walks students through the biggest and most common issues and their quick and simple resolutions. It provides extremely valuable guidance on where to find the documentation and software that is required to keep your UCS system running smoothly. This course is a must for anyone wanting to master the Cisco UCS system.
